00:59:33,812 --> 00:59:34,791
They were frightened.

1088
00:59:35,148 --> 00:59:36,474
Said they'd never come back.

1089
00:59:47,935 --> 00:59:49,684
I was fond of Pierrot.

1090
00:59:49,732 --> 00:59:51,926
I regarded him almost as a son.

1091
00:59:51,968 --> 00:59:53,657
Well, he's closed his umbrella.

1092
00:59:53,716 --> 00:59:55,024
Pepe,

1093
00:59:55,388 --> 00:59:57,739
there's no use in thinking about Pierrot.

1094
00:59:57,800 --> 00:59:59,528
Don't you tell me what to think.

1095
01:00:02,568 --> 01:00:04,164
This a sad thing.

1096
01:00:04,199 --> 01:00:05,123
Are you finished?

1097
01:00:05,398 --> 01:00:06,478
I beg your pardon.

1098
01:00:06,478 --> 01:00:09,507
You were fond of him. That's enough.

1099
01:00:09,747 --> 01:00:11,160
Can't a man talk?

1100
01:00:41,524 --> 01:00:42,802
Well?
Well.

1101
01:00:43,398 --> 01:00:44,266
It's finished.

1102
01:00:54,291 --> 01:00:56,717
I did everything you would have done, Pepe.

1103
01:00:57,781 --> 01:00:59,901
I was all alone at the cemetery.

1104
01:00:59,955 --> 01:01:02,148
I followed the custom of your people.

1105
01:01:02,354 --> 01:01:04,481
A handful of earth on the body.

1106
01:01:04,963 --> 01:01:05,978
And flowers

1107
01:01:06,283 --> 01:01:09,357
to make him feel at home in such a strange place.

1108
01:01:13,854 --> 01:01:18,892
It's hard not to be able to go sown to say
goodbye to your friend on his last journey.

1109
01:01:55,118 --> 01:01:56,518
I'm your friend, Pepe.

1110
01:01:56,972 --> 01:02:00,580
I lnow how you feel; you'er a prisoner in the Casbah.

1111
01:02:00,625 --> 01:02:04,413
But the day will come when they won't be able to prevent your leaving.

1112
01:02:04,640 --> 01:02:07,272
You'll go out of the Casbah in spite of them all.

1113
01:02:07,320 --> 01:02:12,534
I'll get out whenever I wish.
When you go, you'll go quietly the way Pierrot went.

1114
01:02:12,591 --> 01:02:13,650
Feet first.

1115
01:02:14,059 --> 01:02:15,184
Be patient.

1116
01:02:15,570 --> 01:02:20,088
When the time comes, they'll take off their hats and let you pass.

1117
01:02:20,128 --> 01:02:21,451
I'll go out alive.

1118
01:02:24,706 --> 01:02:26,733
I don't think you're as foolish as that.

1119
01:02:33,279 --> 01:02:34,256
Grandperre,

1120
01:02:34,514 --> 01:02:35,708
I've heard enough.

1121
01:02:39,776 --> 01:02:42,293
Music. Singing. Gibberish.

1122
01:02:42,293 --> 01:02:43,704
I'm sorry for you.

1123
01:02:45,055 --> 01:02:45,908
How is she?

1124
01:02:45,965 --> 01:02:46,617
She?

1125
01:02:46,656 --> 01:02:47,483
You know.

1126
01:02:47,555 --> 01:02:50,995
I'm afraid you won't see her again. The last visit was a little too much for her.

1127
01:02:51,034 --> 01:02:53,185
She got a bad impression of the Casbah.

1128
01:02:53,474 --> 01:02:54,191
It's a pity.

1129
01:02:54,802 --> 01:02:58,647
Why should it be a pity?
For your sake since it seems to mean so much to you.

1130
01:02:58,705 --> 01:02:59,535
To me?

1131
01:03:00,196 --> 01:03:02,915
So that's what you're so sorry about.

1132
01:03:02,955 --> 01:03:05,927
Why are you standing there staring at me?

1133
01:03:05,947 --> 01:03:07,133
Do as I tell you.

1134
01:03:07,176 --> 01:03:08,494
Go down.

1135
01:03:09,627 --> 01:03:10,532
And you too.

1136
01:03:10,581 --> 01:03:11,807
Get out.

1137
01:03:12,438 --> 01:03:13,366
I've had enough.

1138
01:03:14,148 --> 01:03:15,074
And you.

1139
01:03:15,533 --> 01:03:17,407
I'm sick of looking at you.

1140
01:03:20,070 --> 01:03:22,351
You seem to be sick of everything.

1141
01:03:22,881 --> 01:03:23,468
Right.

1142
01:03:23,679 --> 01:03:27,310
I'd bring her up to see you again if it were possible, but there's no chance.

1143
01:03:27,370 --> 01:03:28,419
So.

1144
01:03:28,472 --> 01:03:29,967
She's not coming back.

1145
01:03:30,018 --> 01:03:31,394
That's fine.

1146
01:03:31,394 --> 01:03:35,086
What?
All that swell jewelry, you had it right in the palm of your hand.

1147
01:03:35,086 --> 01:03:35,835
That's enough.

1148
01:03:36,045 --> 01:03:38,921
These people who look as if they can tear down everything

1149
01:03:38,977 --> 01:03:41,759
and when a woman looks at them, they get as soft as butter.

1150
01:03:41,804 --> 01:03:44,453
Get out.
Well, I'm not made of butter. Not me.

1151
01:03:44,453 --> 01:03:45,966
Get out.
Ok.

1152
01:03:46,670 --> 01:03:49,366
Your friends have no tact, my dear Pepe.

1153
01:03:49,398 --> 01:03:51,650
They have no respect for the beauty of your anguish.

1154
01:03:51,763 --> 01:03:55,469
I know how it pains you to live among this cattle.

1155
01:03:55,469 --> 01:03:57,973
Let me assure you.
They can't keep me here.

1156
01:03:58,401 --> 01:03:59,462
I'm free.

1157
01:03:59,848 --> 01:04:00,705
Free to go.

1158
01:04:01,193 --> 01:04:02,072
I'm sick of it.

1159
01:04:02,816 --> 01:04:03,761
All of you.

1160
01:04:04,104 --> 01:04:05,912
I'm sick of listening to you.

1161
01:04:06,402 --> 01:04:07,744
And I'm sick of looking at you.

1162
01:04:08,183 --> 01:04:10,171
I'll get out when I feel like it.

1163
01:04:10,241 --> 01:04:11,715
None of you can stop me.

1164
01:04:11,772 --> 01:04:14,163
Listen to me, Pepe.
I don't need your advice.

1165
01:04:14,428 --> 01:04:15,460
None of you.

1166
01:04:15,659 --> 01:04:16,882
I'm free to do as I please.

1167
01:04:16,970 --> 01:04:18,462
Free. You hear that?

1168
01:04:18,498 --> 01:04:19,823
You're walking into a trap.

1169
01:04:19,823 --> 01:04:23,416
You know better.
They can't touch me. I'm going down. Get out of the way.

1170
01:04:23,416 --> 01:04:27,272
Let me. And when I please is now. Get out of my way.

1171
01:04:36,012 --> 01:04:38,122
He's gone mad. He's going down to the town.

1172
01:04:38,122 --> 01:04:39,190
He won't listen.

1173
01:04:59,360 --> 01:04:59,968
Hello.

1174
01:05:05,808 --> 01:05:06,583
Good.

1175
01:05:06,644 --> 01:05:07,848
I'll attend to it.

1176
01:05:07,922 --> 01:05:09,871
Inspector Slimane.

1177
01:05:09,927 --> 01:05:11,885
He says Pepe le Moko is coming out.

1178
01:05:30,587 --> 01:05:31,390
Pepe.

1179
01:05:31,442 --> 01:05:32,531
Pepe, don't go.

1180
01:05:32,586 --> 01:05:33,635
You're mad.

1181
01:05:39,586 --> 01:05:41,316
Pepe, don't go. Please don't go.

1182
01:05:41,600 --> 01:05:44,014
I didn't want to tell you this, but she's up there now

1183
01:05:44,875 --> 01:05:46,838
at your old house waiting for you.

1184
01:06:02,922 --> 01:06:03,831
Where is she?

1185
01:06:07,737 --> 01:06:08,790
Where is she?

1186
01:06:09,415 --> 01:06:10,951
You lied to me, didn't you?

1187
01:06:10,997 --> 01:06:12,632
Answer me. Didn't you?

1188
01:06:13,966 --> 01:06:16,804
It was the only way I could keep you from going.

1189
01:06:17,467 --> 01:06:19,613
If I had asked you not to go for me,

1190
01:06:20,136 --> 01:06:21,429
you wouldn't have listened to me.

1191
01:06:22,700 --> 01:06:23,359
So.

1192
01:06:30,648 --> 01:06:33,683
You ought to be fed up with a fellow like me.

1193
01:06:37,348 --> 01:06:39,994
I didn't know I could make such a fool of myself.

1194
01:06:45,239 --> 01:06:47,605
Ines, have something better than this.

1195
01:06:48,130 --> 01:06:50,052
It's not what you deserve.

1196
01:06:51,916 --> 01:06:53,270
It's what you want.

1197
01:06:54,614 --> 01:06:55,987
Why do you worry about me?

1198
01:06:56,531 --> 01:06:57,456
It's not good.

1199
01:06:57,927 --> 01:06:58,795
I have a sharp

1200
01:06:58,830 --> 01:07:00,785
that brings me luck.

1201
01:07:03,014 --> 01:07:05,433
You brought us both luck this time.

1202
01:07:05,439 --> 01:07:07,629
All the while I went running,

1203
01:07:07,851 --> 01:07:09,481
I kept my hand so.

1204
01:07:10,090 --> 01:07:11,530
But you caught me.

1205
01:07:12,085 --> 01:07:14,321
I didn't know you could run so fast.

1206
01:07:14,844 --> 01:07:16,569
Don't forget; I've had practice.

1207
01:07:16,797 --> 01:07:18,824
But nobody ever caught me before.

1208
01:07:20,617 --> 01:07:22,548
Next time, give me a head start.

1209
01:07:23,856 --> 01:07:25,220
Next time?

1210
01:07:27,246 --> 01:07:28,291
Don't worry.

1211
01:07:28,647 --> 01:07:30,377
Not 'til I catch my breath.

1212
01:07:32,932 --> 01:07:34,576
I'm thirsty.

1213
01:07:34,576 --> 01:07:35,520
I'll get it.

1214
01:07:37,964 --> 01:07:38,976
No you won't.

1215
01:08:22,849 --> 01:08:24,164
Here I am.

1216
01:08:24,604 --> 01:08:26,045
I said I'd be here.

1217
01:08:26,702 --> 01:08:27,592
Well?

1218
01:08:27,872 --> 01:08:29,760
You look as though you've seen a ghost.

1219
01:09:39,389 --> 01:09:40,656
You're beautiful.

1220
01:09:41,362 --> 01:09:42,736
That's easy to say.

1221
01:09:42,754 --> 01:09:44,798
I know a lot of people have told you.

1222
01:09:45,309 --> 01:09:47,234
But what I'm telling you is different. See?

1223
01:09:48,217 --> 01:09:49,882
For me, you're more than that.

1224
01:09:50,172 --> 01:09:51,789
For two years, I've been lost.

1225
01:09:52,161 --> 01:09:53,816
Like walking in my sleep.

1226
01:09:53,816 --> 01:09:55,926
Slowly I wake up. That's you.

1227
01:09:56,625 --> 01:10:00,061
I don't know what I've been doing all that time, waiting for you without knowing it.

1228
01:10:00,823 --> 01:10:02,525
Do you know what you are to me?

1229
01:10:03,440 --> 01:10:05,482
Paris. That's you.

1230
01:10:05,887 --> 01:10:06,523
Paris.

1231
01:10:07,103 --> 01:10:08,561
With you, I escape.

1232
01:10:08,619 --> 01:10:09,311
Follow me?

1233
01:10:09,558 --> 01:10:10,753
The whole town

1234
01:10:10,939 --> 01:10:12,775
is spring morning in Paris.

1235
01:10:13,808 --> 01:10:15,305
You're lovely.

1236
01:10:16,083 --> 01:10:17,110
You're marvelous.

1237
01:10:18,560 --> 01:10:20,679
And do you know what you remind me of?

1238
01:10:22,667 --> 01:10:23,732
The subway.

1239
01:10:29,286 --> 01:10:30,779
Close your eyes.

1240
01:10:33,691 --> 01:10:34,839
Listen.

1241
01:10:36,625 --> 01:10:37,728
Can you hear it?

1242
01:10:38,687 --> 01:10:40,479
That's my heart beating.

1243
01:10:40,539 --> 01:10:42,820
Dose it go like a subway train?

1244
01:10:43,151 --> 01:10:44,187
Faster.

1245
01:10:45,319 --> 01:10:46,881
You're all silk,

1246
01:10:46,936 --> 01:10:48,788
and you jingle when you walk.

1247
01:10:48,788 --> 01:10:51,431
And with all that shi shi, you make me think of the subway.

1248
01:10:51,431 --> 01:10:52,572
Isn't that funny?

1249
01:10:52,572 --> 01:10:53,894
And potato chips

1250
01:10:53,972 --> 01:10:55,774
and coffee on the boulevard.

1251
01:11:00,431 --> 01:11:02,055
What did you do before?

1252
01:11:02,438 --> 01:11:03,287
Before what?

1253
01:11:04,488 --> 01:11:05,691
Before the jewels.

1254
01:11:06,429 --> 01:11:07,726
I wanted them.

1255
01:11:19,943 --> 01:11:21,189
It's late.

1256
01:11:21,266 --> 01:11:22,400
I must go.

1257
01:11:25,687 --> 01:11:27,328
Suppose you don't come tomorrow.

1258
01:11:30,152 --> 01:11:31,486
Suppose I don't.

1259
01:11:32,245 --> 01:11:34,840
Can't you ever get away from the Casbah?

1260
01:11:35,093 --> 01:11:36,044
Why do you ask?

1261
01:11:36,254 --> 01:11:37,023
Can't you?

1262
01:11:37,078 --> 01:11:37,496
No.

1263
01:11:37,789 --> 01:11:38,992
I'm caught here

1264
01:11:39,228 --> 01:11:40,842
like a bear in a hole,

1265
01:11:40,919 --> 01:11:43,257
dogs barking, hunters all around,

1266
01:11:43,298 --> 01:11:44,352
no way out of it.

1267
01:11:45,256 --> 01:11:46,239
Do you like that?

1268
01:11:55,201 --> 01:11:56,755
Maybe it's lucky for you.

1269
01:11:58,038 --> 01:11:59,192
I don't like it.

1270
01:11:59,241 --> 01:12:00,519
And it's not lucky.

1271
01:12:01,258 --> 01:12:02,116
You're right.

1272
01:12:03,039 --> 01:12:04,943
If you don't come back, I might do anything.

1273
01:12:05,347 --> 01:12:07,437
I might go down to the hotel to get you.

1274
01:12:08,416 --> 01:12:09,929
Tomorrow, Pepe.

1275
01:12:10,006 --> 01:12:11,048
Tomorrow?

1276
01:12:11,690 --> 01:12:13,211
I never break a promise.

1277
01:12:34,018 --> 01:12:35,183
You smell good.

1278
01:12:37,076 --> 01:12:38,143
The subway?

1279
01:12:38,606 --> 01:12:40,321
Streamlined.

1280
01:13:30,528 --> 01:13:31,210
Hey.

1281
01:13:31,478 --> 01:13:32,298
Anton.

1282
01:13:34,895 --> 01:13:35,625
Tomorrow.

1283
01:13:36,378 --> 01:13:37,303
5 o'clock.

1284
01:13:55,714 --> 01:13:56,663
Did you get them?

1285
01:13:57,268 --> 01:13:57,911
What?

1286
01:13:57,991 --> 01:13:59,333
The hardware.

1287
01:14:00,510 --> 01:14:01,839
What's the matter with you?

1288
01:14:01,924 --> 01:14:04,790
If you didn't get the jewels, you're simply wasting your time.

1289
01:14:04,790 --> 01:14:06,305
What were you doing in there?

1290
01:14:06,448 --> 01:14:07,913
Where?
There.

1291
01:14:08,470 --> 01:14:09,745
You're mistaken.

1292
01:14:10,317 --> 01:14:11,499
We were not there.

1293
01:14:12,252 --> 01:14:13,405
Say that again.

1294
01:14:15,307 --> 01:14:16,651
We were in Paris.

1295
01:14:16,770 --> 01:14:17,574
What?

1296
01:14:20,012 --> 01:14:21,279
Okay.

1297
01:14:43,000 --> 01:14:46,400
Life is simple if you try to enjoy before you die every bit of happiness along the way.

1298
01:14:48,600 --> 01:14:51,200
Take the joy that comes to you.

1299
01:14:51,200 --> 01:14:53,500
Suddenly the world is too with the song that keeps you dancing every day.

1300
01:14:53,500 --> 01:14:55,700
That's the life.

1301
01:14:55,700 --> 01:14:58,200
Fall in love and life is sunny.

1302
01:14:58,200 --> 01:15:00,900
That's the life you don't need money

1303
01:15:00,900 --> 01:15:04,100
if you've got a little honey in your arms.

1304
01:15:04,100 --> 01:15:06,300
That's the life.

1305
01:15:06,300 --> 01:15:08,900
I'm in heaven and I know it.

1306
01:15:08,900 --> 01:15:11,500
Can I help it if I show it?

1307
01:15:11,500 --> 01:15:13,872
Life is sweet as can be for me.

1308
01:15:13,872 --> 01:15:17,600
Love is very necessary.

1309
01:15:17,600 --> 01:15:20,200
Fall in love and you'll be happy. That's the life.

1310
01:15:20,200 --> 01:15:23,300
You don't know just what you miss if you live without a kiss

1311
01:15:23,300 --> 01:15:26,000
for a kiss can bring your winter into spring.

1312
01:15:26,000 --> 01:15:31,000
Everybody will agree. If you fall in love like me, you'll be happy, you will laugh, and you will sing.

1313
01:15:31,000 --> 01:15:33,400
That's the life.

1314
01:15:33,400 --> 01:15:35,800
That's the life we should be living.

1315
01:15:35,800 --> 01:15:40,800
Kiss morning, noon, and evening. That's the life that I'll be living.

1316
01:15:40,800 --> 01:15:44,300
That's the moon. That's the life.

1317
01:15:44,300 --> 01:15:46,800
There is nothing like that feeling.

1318
01:15:46,800 --> 01:15:49,400
Tell me what is more appealing

1319
01:15:49,400 --> 01:15:51,200
than the feeling you're in love

1320
01:15:51,200 --> 01:15:52,800
for sure.

1321
01:15:52,800 --> 01:15:57,900
Love is very necessary. Fall in love and you'll be happy. That's the life.

1322
01:15:58,000 --> 01:16:01,100
Love is very necessary.

1323
01:16:01,100 --> 01:16:03,911
Fall in love and you'll be happy. That's the life.

1324
01:16:03,911 --> 01:16:05,599
Pepe, what's happened?

1325
01:16:05,652 --> 01:16:06,618
Don't you know?

1326
01:16:06,618 --> 01:16:07,805
It's a holiday.

1327
01:16:07,861 --> 01:16:09,356
No, I didn't know what day it is.

1328
01:16:09,356 --> 01:16:11,616
It's Sunday. Everyone gets a holiday.

1329
01:16:11,616 --> 01:16:12,977
But it's not Sunday.

1330
01:16:13,002 --> 01:16:14,580
If I say so, it's Sunday.

1331
01:16:14,580 --> 01:16:18,617
It's Thursday.
That's the trouble with you; you always think it's Thursday.

1332
01:16:18,617 --> 01:16:21,594
I didn't think so yesterday.

1333
01:16:21,646 --> 01:16:23,937
Just as a favor to me, let it be Sunday.

1334
01:16:23,988 --> 01:16:26,093
I want to stroll on the boulevard.

1335
01:16:28,499 --> 01:16:30,373
I have a date at the Place Blanche.

1336
01:16:38,598 --> 01:16:39,936
Hello, everybody.

1337
01:16:40,498 --> 01:16:41,715
How do you like my singing?

1338
01:16:41,786 --> 01:16:43,080
What's the good of it?

1339
01:16:44,189 --> 01:16:46,711
You ought to appreciate the finer things of life.

1340
01:16:46,711 --> 01:16:48,064
Who? Him?

1341
01:16:49,254 --> 01:16:51,354
When you feel like that, sing.

1342
01:16:51,354 --> 01:16:52,628
It quiets the nerves.

1343
01:16:53,857 --> 01:16:56,727
You seem pleased. You've seen her again.

1344
01:16:56,774 --> 01:16:57,777
Wouldn't you like to know.

1345
01:16:57,777 --> 01:16:59,816
Oh, well. If you don't want to confide in me.

1346
01:16:59,816 --> 01:17:02,281
Well, our inspector got himself a haircut.

1347
01:17:02,293 --> 01:17:03,371
Did she come back?

1348
01:17:03,371 --> 01:17:04,628
A regular Romeo.

1349
01:17:04,628 --> 01:17:05,968
You ought to get a permanent wave.

1350
01:17:06,048 --> 01:17:07,673
You're expecting her again today?

1351
01:17:07,750 --> 01:17:10,742
The trouble with you, Inspector, is that you do too much inspecting.

1352
01:17:10,742 --> 01:17:11,301
Now,

1353
01:17:11,462 --> 01:17:13,252
not a word about what I have told you.

1354
01:17:13,431 --> 01:17:14,893
Just between ourselves,

1355
01:17:15,687 --> 01:17:16,353
yup.

1356
01:17:45,837 --> 01:17:47,001
Inspector.

1357
01:17:47,081 --> 01:17:48,351
Good afternoon.

1358
01:17:48,850 --> 01:17:50,823
I was puzzled when you phoned.

1359
01:17:51,085 --> 01:17:53,887
My mission is a rather delicate one

1360
01:17:53,937 --> 01:17:55,676
but necessary.

1361
01:17:56,599 --> 01:17:58,318
I merely wish to suggest that

1362
01:17:58,393 --> 01:18:01,540
your fiance is a little too fond of

1363
01:18:02,515 --> 01:18:06,123
shall we say, the local color of the Casbah.

1364
01:18:07,556 --> 01:18:08,721
What is all this?

1365
01:18:09,600 --> 01:18:12,385
The Casbah is hardly the place for a woman alone.

1366
01:18:12,428 --> 01:18:14,264
She attracts too much attention,

1367
01:18:14,326 --> 01:18:16,291
excites too much desire.

1368
01:18:17,069 --> 01:18:20,538
If we, naturally, wish to protect her from any embarrassment.

1369
01:18:21,776 --> 01:18:25,164
Further embarrassment can very easily be avoided.

1370
01:18:25,628 --> 01:18:28,468
She must not return to the Casbah.

1371
01:18:35,558 --> 01:18:36,297
Come in.

1372
01:18:39,499 --> 01:18:40,693
Sorry to disturb you.

1373
01:18:43,297 --> 01:18:44,338
You're going out?

1374
01:18:44,421 --> 01:18:45,310
Looks that way.

1375
01:18:45,310 --> 01:18:46,257
Where are you going?

1376
01:18:46,458 --> 01:18:47,252
A walk.

1377
01:18:47,495 --> 01:18:48,439
But where?

1378
01:18:48,500 --> 01:18:50,180
In the Champs-lyses.

1379
01:18:50,234 --> 01:18:52,470
May I ask you to give me a sensible answer?

1380
01:18:52,521 --> 01:18:55,563
Then ask me a sensible question. Where could I go?

1381
01:18:55,986 --> 01:18:57,908
I don't know anyone in Algiers.

1382
01:18:58,584 --> 01:19:00,120
I just walk straight ahead.

1383
01:19:00,165 --> 01:19:01,322
Straight ahead?

1384
01:19:01,568 --> 01:19:03,102
And where does that take you?

1385
01:19:03,102 --> 01:19:04,717
I'll know when I get there.

1386
01:19:04,717 --> 01:19:05,390
No you won't

1387
01:19:05,948 --> 01:19:06,814
because you're not going.

1388
01:19:06,963 --> 01:19:08,372
Oh, yes, my dear.

1389
01:19:08,602 --> 01:19:10,094
Your hotel bores me.

1390
01:19:10,148 --> 01:19:12,139
The head waiter looks like an undertaker.

1391
01:19:12,410 --> 01:19:14,851
An every time I step into this apartment

1392
01:19:14,900 --> 01:19:16,952
it looks more like a funeral parlor.

1393
01:19:17,005 --> 01:19:18,221
Goodbye, darling.

1394
01:19:20,445 --> 01:19:21,650
I know where you're going.

1395
01:19:21,650 --> 01:19:23,541
Ah?
You're going to the Casbah.

1396
01:19:23,541 --> 01:19:25,521
So?
You go there every day.

1397
01:19:25,576 --> 01:19:27,555
Do I?
To meet Pepe le Moko.

1398
01:19:30,097 --> 01:19:32,029
So now you're spying on me?

1399
01:19:33,937 --> 01:19:35,148
You're going to be my wife.

1400
01:19:35,398 --> 01:19:37,162
You don't make it a very pleasant prospect.

1401
01:19:37,162 --> 01:19:39,158
And I won't allow you to behave like this.

1402
01:19:39,480 --> 01:19:40,718
I'm glad you told me.

1403
01:19:40,782 --> 01:19:41,778
What do you mean?

1404
01:19:43,761 --> 01:19:44,933
We've got to be honest.

1405
01:19:45,528 --> 01:19:47,084
Why do you think I'm marrying you?

1406
01:19:47,496 --> 01:19:49,411
Look at yourself, and now look at me.

1407
01:19:49,463 --> 01:19:50,834
I've never lied to you.

1408
01:19:51,091 --> 01:19:55,062
You knew I didn't love you when I promised to marry you, and you though it was alright.

1409
01:19:55,124 --> 01:19:57,548
Until we are married, I'll do as I please.

1410
01:19:57,616 --> 01:19:58,828
That's fair enough.

1411
01:19:59,342 --> 01:20:00,829
I forbid you to go.

1412
01:20:01,342 --> 01:20:02,346
It's a waste of time.

1413
01:20:02,694 --> 01:20:05,316
If you go now, there'll be no use in you coming back.

1414
01:20:06,145 --> 01:20:08,649
You've thought it all out pretty clearly. Haven't you?

1415
01:20:08,712 --> 01:20:10,846
And I advise you to do the same.

1416
01:20:11,387 --> 01:20:12,199
Alright.

1417
01:20:12,601 --> 01:20:13,280
Goodbye.

1418
01:20:14,444 --> 01:20:15,946
Do it, Gaby. Don't.

1419
01:20:20,324 --> 01:20:21,123
No.

1420
01:20:21,708 --> 01:20:22,270
What?

1421
01:20:22,336 --> 01:20:24,017
You can't go to the Casbah.

1422
01:20:24,074 --> 01:20:24,858
But really.

1423
01:20:24,935 --> 01:20:26,992
Your fiance was trying to spare you.

1424
01:20:27,143 --> 01:20:29,176
He didn't want to tell you the truth as I told it to him.

1425
01:20:29,794 --> 01:20:33,456
An attempt was made to capture Pepe le Moko this afternoon.

1426
01:20:33,456 --> 01:20:35,326
The attempt was successful.

1427
01:20:35,450 --> 01:20:36,321
He was taken?

1428
01:20:36,432 --> 01:20:37,382
Not alive.

1429
01:20:37,780 --> 01:20:38,805
He was killed.

1430
01:21:26,656 --> 01:21:29,630
I just came to tell you, it's Thursday.

1431
01:21:30,671 --> 01:21:31,533
I know.

1432
01:21:32,549 --> 01:21:34,485
I was right all the time.

1433
01:21:34,723 --> 01:21:36,738
You see, I'm not just a fool as you think.

1434
01:21:38,745 --> 01:21:40,794
So this is the Place Blanche.

1435
01:21:42,779 --> 01:21:44,931
It's not much fun on Thursday, is it?

1436
01:21:45,023 --> 01:21:47,133
It doesn't seem like Paris.

1437
01:22:01,055 --> 01:22:02,476
What's got into him?

1438
01:22:03,378 --> 01:22:05,772
Weren't you ever disappointed in love?

1439
01:22:05,832 --> 01:22:07,097
Yes. Badly.

1440
01:22:08,082 --> 01:22:10,287
I'll try to please you.

1441
01:22:10,954 --> 01:22:12,508
I'm like Pepe.

1442
01:22:12,952 --> 01:22:14,433
I like 'em with diamonds.

1443
01:22:14,966 --> 01:22:16,370
Now he's missed his chance.

1444
01:22:17,452 --> 01:22:22,612
So I guess I'll have to go downtown and give my personal attention to madam's hardware.

1445
01:22:24,019 --> 01:22:25,192
What steamer?

1446
01:22:25,945 --> 01:22:28,498
The Ville d'Algers? Ten o'clock? Good.

1447
01:22:28,556 --> 01:22:29,717
Make the reservation.

1448
01:22:30,925 --> 01:22:31,889
Are you leaving?

1449
01:22:33,060 --> 01:22:35,154
I suppose you won't stay for the funeral.

1450
01:22:38,415 --> 01:22:40,114
Four. First class.

1451
01:22:40,607 --> 01:22:42,485
Oh. Send up some whiskey and soda.

1452
01:22:44,933 --> 01:22:45,857
You'll have a drink.

1453
01:22:46,679 --> 01:22:47,779
Just a short one.

1454
01:22:48,314 --> 01:22:49,450
Make you feel better.

1455
01:23:01,692 --> 01:23:02,715
Anything wrong?

1456
01:23:04,007 --> 01:23:05,111
Why don't you sing?

1457
01:23:05,389 --> 01:23:06,765
Why don't you mind your own business?

1458
01:23:07,132 --> 01:23:08,036
I am.

1459
01:23:08,255 --> 01:23:10,538
Only I just though you might be interested.

1460
01:23:10,863 --> 01:23:12,383
I'm going downtown.

1461
01:23:12,783 --> 01:23:13,610
What for?

1462
01:23:13,693 --> 01:23:15,034
Unlike you, I'm bored.

1463
01:23:15,516 --> 01:23:16,914
Anything in your mind?

1464
01:23:16,955 --> 01:23:18,962
Just to look things over.

1465
01:23:19,342 --> 01:23:22,299
-When are you going?
-Now. No use to see a lawyer about it.

1466
01:23:22,391 --> 01:23:24,273
-Do me a favor.
-Sure.

1467
01:23:24,403 --> 01:23:25,791
I want you to deliver a letter.

1468
01:23:25,948 --> 01:23:27,684
I'd take anything that isn't loaded.

1469
01:23:29,052 --> 01:23:31,451
Ok. I get the idea.

1470
01:23:31,528 --> 01:23:33,628
Maybe I don't look like Cupid, but I'll manage.

1471
01:23:34,838 --> 01:23:35,898
Pen and paper.

1472
01:23:36,407 --> 01:23:38,497
Go to the servants' entrance.

1473
01:23:38,555 --> 01:23:39,895
Give someone a good tip.

1474
01:23:40,044 --> 01:23:41,834
And tell them you've got to have an answer.

1475
01:23:41,883 --> 01:23:44,862
Don't worry. I won't come back empty handed.

1476
01:23:45,812 --> 01:23:47,323
I'll wait for you at your house.

1477
01:23:47,382 --> 01:23:49,672
I'll be back in two hours. Tell Tania.

1478
01:23:49,951 --> 01:23:50,672
Good luck.

1479
01:23:58,897 --> 01:24:00,078
What time is it?

1480
01:24:00,944 --> 01:24:02,127
9 o'clock.

1481
01:24:02,740 --> 01:24:03,913
Is that all?

1482
01:24:04,208 --> 01:24:05,359
In the morning.

1483
01:24:05,873 --> 01:24:07,479
Sun is out.

1484
01:24:07,885 --> 01:24:09,416
I slept all that time?

1485
01:24:11,231 --> 01:24:12,104
Carlos?

1486
01:24:12,341 --> 01:24:13,586
He hasn't come back.

1487
01:24:14,134 --> 01:24:15,326
He hasn't come back?

1488
01:24:15,853 --> 01:24:17,438
I sat up all night.

1489
01:24:19,392 --> 01:24:22,470
I'd like to see him back with what I've got to tell him.

1490
01:24:23,200 --> 01:24:25,508
This time, I'll make him listen to me.

1491
01:24:26,880 --> 01:24:28,216
Poor Carlos.

1492
01:24:28,342 --> 01:24:32,317
Same old story.

1493
01:24:32,788 --> 01:24:33,745
Well.

1494
01:24:33,991 --> 01:24:35,241
Life is like that.

1495
01:24:35,241 --> 01:24:35,885
Yeah.

1496
01:24:36,128 --> 01:24:39,654
And we're dumb enough to hang on because we don't want to stir it when.

1497
01:24:41,686 --> 01:24:42,438
Smart.

1498
01:24:44,147 --> 01:24:45,400
Is Pepe here?

1499
01:24:45,460 --> 01:24:46,403
What do you want?

1500
01:24:46,686 --> 01:24:49,790
We've been looking for you everywhere. Why weren't you at home?

1501
01:24:50,054 --> 01:24:51,172
Because I'm here.

1502
01:24:51,231 --> 01:24:52,529
What do you want, L'Arbi?

1503
01:24:53,943 --> 01:24:55,342
I must speak to you alone.

1504
01:24:55,439 --> 01:24:56,446
What's the matter with us?

1505
01:24:56,528 --> 01:24:57,749
Ever got small pox?

1506
01:24:57,816 --> 01:25:00,338
-It's alright; you can talk.
-Pepe, I'm ashamed of myself.

1507
01:25:00,421 --> 01:25:01,544
What's new about that?

1508
01:25:01,623 --> 01:25:03,922
-Oh, It's more than you think.
-I doubt that.

1509
01:25:03,979 --> 01:25:05,654
Go ahead and insult me.

1510
01:25:05,813 --> 01:25:06,864
I deserve it.

1511
01:25:06,864 --> 01:25:08,022
You flatter yourself.

1512
01:25:08,107 --> 01:25:10,489
It's about the letter from Pierrot's mother.

1513
01:25:10,562 --> 01:25:13,781
I brought it and gave it to Aicha, but I didn't know it was from the police.

1514
01:25:13,871 --> 01:25:17,140
If I had known the letter was written by Regis, I wouldn't have done it. Never.

1515
01:25:17,197 --> 01:25:17,972
Go on.

1516
01:25:18,959 --> 01:25:20,833
It was really a woman who gave me the letter.

1517
01:25:21,640 --> 01:25:24,760
I, if I had known the truth, I wouldn't have touched it.

1518
01:25:24,842 --> 01:25:26,078
I'm an informer.

1519
01:25:26,152 --> 01:25:28,288
Yes, but I wouldn't have done a thing like that.

1520
01:25:28,370 --> 01:25:30,311
Oh, you're only half an informer.

1521
01:25:30,311 --> 01:25:31,671
The other half is alright.

1522
01:25:32,060 --> 01:25:33,469
Oh, that's why I'm here.

1523
01:25:33,560 --> 01:25:34,266
For what?

1524
01:25:34,907 --> 01:25:38,838
I couldn't stand it any longer. Forgive me, Pepe.

1525
01:25:38,838 --> 01:25:41,475
Alright. Stop grovelling; it makes me sick.

1526
01:25:41,537 --> 01:25:43,276
I want you to have a good opinion of me.

1527
01:25:43,383 --> 01:25:44,133
So?

1528
01:25:44,780 --> 01:25:46,379
I want you to believe me.

1529
01:25:46,446 --> 01:25:47,575
That's why I'm here,

1530
01:25:47,862 --> 01:25:48,852
to tell you

1531
01:25:48,917 --> 01:25:50,872
they got Carlos.

1532
01:25:50,953 --> 01:25:52,223
What about Carlos?

1533
01:25:52,670 --> 01:25:54,188
The police took him.

1534
01:25:54,249 --> 01:25:58,352
-How much did you sell him for?
-I wouldn't be here if I'd sold him.

1535
01:25:58,908 --> 01:26:00,685
First Pierrot, then Carlos.

1536
01:26:00,751 --> 01:26:02,948
Bad luck always runs in threes.

1537
01:26:03,067 --> 01:26:04,567
Your turn will be next, Pepe.

1538
01:26:04,625 --> 01:26:05,996
Don't be so sure.

1539
01:26:06,290 --> 01:26:07,398
So they arrested him.

1540
01:26:07,660 --> 01:26:08,471
Who did it?

1541
01:26:08,535 --> 01:26:09,646
Inspector Louvain.

1542
01:26:09,756 --> 01:26:11,880
They were about a dozen of them surrounding him.

1543
01:26:12,350 --> 01:26:13,834
Was there any shooting?

1544
01:26:13,930 --> 01:26:16,748
No, no. They managed very quietly in a nice way.

1545
01:26:17,022 --> 01:26:18,429
What did you have to do with it?

1546
01:26:18,520 --> 01:26:20,877
I was at the police station when they brought Carlos in.

1547
01:26:20,961 --> 01:26:22,765
I had the chance to see him in his cell.

1548
01:26:22,845 --> 01:26:23,921
They gave me a letter,

1549
01:26:23,992 --> 01:26:25,173
the one you had given him.

1550
01:26:25,262 --> 01:26:26,924
Told me to take it to the hotel.

1551
01:26:26,938 --> 01:26:29,824
Every time there is a letter, he is the one that brings it.

1552
01:26:29,893 --> 01:26:30,803
It looks funny to me.

1553
01:26:30,803 --> 01:26:31,636
Be quiet.

1554
01:26:31,636 --> 01:26:34,351
Oh, I am to be quiet while you write letters to other women?

1555
01:26:34,351 --> 01:26:35,148
Never mind that.

1556
01:26:35,148 --> 01:26:36,301
You never wrote a letter to me.

1557
01:26:36,301 --> 01:26:37,039
Shut up.

1558
01:26:38,359 --> 01:26:40,735
So you went to the hotel with the letter.

1559
01:26:40,818 --> 01:26:41,988
I did it for you, Pepe.

1560
01:26:42,534 --> 01:26:43,330
You get it?

1561
01:26:43,367 --> 01:26:43,951
What?

1562
01:26:44,658 --> 01:26:45,577
The answer.

1563
01:26:45,643 --> 01:26:47,068
Oh, she wouldn't write you.

1564
01:26:47,068 --> 01:26:48,049
But she couldn't.

1565
01:26:48,125 --> 01:26:49,504
She's being closely watched.

1566
01:26:49,599 --> 01:26:51,002
But she expects you this morning.

1567
01:26:51,209 --> 01:26:52,973
You can go down without any risk.

1568
01:26:53,033 --> 01:26:53,767
Go to her.

1569
01:26:53,835 --> 01:26:55,952
Service entrance in the back of the hotel.

1570
01:26:56,015 --> 01:26:57,507
She'll be watching from her window.

1571
01:26:57,561 --> 01:26:58,640
Is that all?

1572
01:26:58,746 --> 01:27:00,468
She wants to come out, but she couldn't get away.

1573
01:27:00,468 --> 01:27:03,559
-You're not going out, Pepe. You can't.
-I told you to shut up.

1574
01:27:04,686 --> 01:27:05,473
Go on.

1575
01:27:05,758 --> 01:27:07,788
She's waiting for me to bring the answer.

1576
01:27:08,322 --> 01:27:09,662
What shall I tell her?

1577
01:27:10,437 --> 01:27:11,969
She's waiting for it.

1578
01:27:12,039 --> 01:27:12,926
Yes.

1579
01:27:13,504 --> 01:27:15,306
I'll take the answer myself.

1580
01:27:16,002 --> 01:27:17,304
You wait here.

1581
01:27:19,389 --> 01:27:20,258
But Pepe.

1582
01:27:20,362 --> 01:27:21,240
Don't worry.

1583
01:27:21,631 --> 01:27:23,620
My friends will take good care of you

1584
01:27:24,006 --> 01:27:25,100
until I come back.

1585
01:27:27,165 --> 01:27:28,661
But she expects me.

1586
01:27:29,405 --> 01:27:29,824
What?

1587
01:27:31,365 --> 01:27:32,404
Nothing.

1588
01:27:33,718 --> 01:27:34,728
I'll wait.

1589
01:27:35,865 --> 01:27:36,915
Tell me.

1590
01:27:37,088 --> 01:27:38,220
What about Carlos?

1591
01:27:39,118 --> 01:27:40,312
Didn't he say anything else?

1592
01:27:40,807 --> 01:27:41,423
Nothing.

1593
01:27:41,905 --> 01:27:42,966
They search him?

1594
01:27:43,341 --> 01:27:43,905
Yes.

1595
01:27:45,114 --> 01:27:46,875
Then they took away the five thousand.

1596
01:27:46,875 --> 01:27:47,608
Yes.

1597
01:27:49,609 --> 01:27:53,052
-You're sure he didn't slip the five thousand to you?
-No.

1598
01:27:53,139 --> 01:27:54,202
You're sure?

1599
01:27:55,415 --> 01:27:56,137
What?

1600
01:27:56,771 --> 01:27:59,348
Lovain took the money. I saw him put it in his desk.

1601
01:28:01,681 --> 01:28:04,195
You said Gaby couldn't write because she was watched.

1602
01:28:04,267 --> 01:28:04,838
Yes.

1603
01:28:05,244 --> 01:28:08,992
But in a little while she'll be able to see me.

1604
01:28:09,687 --> 01:28:10,828
That's funny.

1605
01:28:11,393 --> 01:28:12,678
He's going to move away.

1606
01:28:12,765 --> 01:28:13,949
Oh, I see.

1607
01:28:14,454 --> 01:28:16,712
-But why couldn't she write to me?
-He was there.

1608
01:28:17,120 --> 01:28:18,445
But she talked to you.

1609
01:28:18,528 --> 01:28:19,859
Because.

1610
01:28:19,859 --> 01:28:21,377
Because you don't know.

1611
01:28:21,650 --> 01:28:24,428
Now there is another thing that doesn't fit in your story.

1612
01:28:24,667 --> 01:28:28,152
How was Louvain able to take 5000 francs from Carlos

1613
01:28:28,225 --> 01:28:29,901
when Carlos didn't have a hundred?

1614
01:28:29,958 --> 01:28:30,828
I don't know.

1615
01:28:32,845 --> 01:28:35,477
Do you think Carlos is dumb enough to give you my letter?

1616
01:28:35,477 --> 01:28:36,420
All joking aside.

1617
01:28:37,089 --> 01:28:39,608
Do you think me so stupid as to believe he would give it to you?

1618
01:28:39,769 --> 01:28:41,774
-All joking aside.
-I give you my word.

1619
01:28:43,276 --> 01:28:45,577
-And then I will go down to see her.
-Yes.

1620
01:28:45,646 --> 01:28:47,420
A woman who is closely watched,

1621
01:28:47,420 --> 01:28:49,229
it's funny the way she can do things.

1622
01:28:49,229 --> 01:28:50,426
Now I've laughed enough!

1623
01:28:50,514 --> 01:28:51,263
Do you hear me?

1624
01:28:51,351 --> 01:28:52,200
You've made a fool of me!

1625
01:28:55,171 --> 01:28:56,408
Carlos was arrested.

1626
01:29:02,031 --> 01:29:03,062
Now tell me what happened.

1627
01:29:04,715 --> 01:29:07,197
Shall I break your neck to refresh your memory?

1628
01:29:07,362 --> 01:29:08,165
No, Pepe.

1629
01:29:09,662 --> 01:29:10,763
Slimane planned it all.

1630
01:29:10,763 --> 01:29:11,258
Yeah?

1631
01:29:11,258 --> 01:29:12,424
He told me to come for you.

1632
01:29:12,424 --> 01:29:14,183
- Go on.
 - He thinks you'll come down.

1633
01:29:14,251 --> 01:29:14,635
- Then?

1634
01:29:14,635 --> 01:29:16,295
The hotel is surrounded, they're waiting.

1635
01:29:16,389 --> 01:29:17,571
Did you see the girl?

1636
01:29:17,715 --> 01:29:18,300
No.

1637
01:29:18,366 --> 01:29:19,774
Why didn't she come up yesterday?

1638
01:29:19,774 --> 01:29:21,315
He told her you'd been killed.

1639
01:29:25,258 --> 01:29:28,152
Slimane planned the whole thing.

1640
01:29:28,700 --> 01:29:29,870
Is that all?

1641
01:29:29,870 --> 01:29:30,890
Yes.

1642
01:29:30,890 --> 01:29:32,750
Thanks.

1643
01:29:46,125 --> 01:29:47,763
You can't do it, Pepe.

1644
01:29:47,982 --> 01:29:50,034
You can't leave me. What have I done?

1645
01:29:51,077 --> 01:29:53,265
It has nothing to do with you, Ines.

1646
01:29:53,548 --> 01:29:56,093
You're a good kid, but this can't be helped.

1647
01:29:56,292 --> 01:29:57,530
It's not your fault.

1648
01:29:58,330 --> 01:30:01,057
I won't let you do it. I won't let you. You'll be killed.

1649
01:30:01,136 --> 01:30:02,245
Blame it on the Casbah.

1650
01:30:02,245 --> 01:30:05,564
It's for her. You don't care about anything else, so you're throwing away your life.

1651
01:30:05,583 --> 01:30:06,645
But it's my own life.

1652
01:30:06,645 --> 01:30:10,071
Don't do it, Pepe. Don't go. Listen to me.

1653
01:30:10,071 --> 01:30:10,983
Pepe.

1654
01:31:52,320 --> 01:31:53,650
Wait.

1655
01:32:47,456 --> 01:32:49,084
We didn't expect you.

1656
01:32:49,157 --> 01:32:50,716
He's not coming here.

1657
01:32:51,140 --> 01:32:52,423
He's gone to the boat.

1658
01:32:52,689 --> 01:32:54,372
You expect me to believe that?

1659
01:32:54,465 --> 01:32:56,385
He is going away with her.

1660
01:32:59,358 --> 01:33:01,222
So you're the one to betray him.

1661
01:33:01,818 --> 01:33:03,267
You couldn't wait to run to me.

1662
01:33:03,911 --> 01:33:08,390
You call it love, but it means you'd kill him before you'd let him go free. That's what you've done.

1663
01:33:08,623 --> 01:33:11,202
Sure as if you'd held a gun in your hands.

1664
01:33:11,690 --> 01:33:13,314
I couldn't let him go.

1665
01:33:13,394 --> 01:33:15,145
I couldn't lose him.

1666
01:33:17,263 --> 01:33:20,330
I thought I'd figured all the moves, but I miscalculated.

1667
01:33:21,557 --> 01:33:22,804
I didn't think of you.

1668
01:33:22,899 --> 01:33:23,888
That's just fine.

1669
01:33:25,829 --> 01:33:28,608
In a few more minutes, it might have been put of our hands.

1670
01:33:30,094 --> 01:33:30,939
Don't go.

1671
01:33:30,941 --> 01:33:32,301
-Give him a chance.
-I did.

1672
01:33:32,301 --> 01:33:34,314
But you knew. You planned it this way.

1673
01:33:34,314 --> 01:33:36,441
So he'd walk into a trap. And he's done it

1674
01:33:36,581 --> 01:33:37,483
with your help.

1675
01:33:37,555 --> 01:33:38,153
Come on.

1676
01:34:38,713 --> 01:34:41,682
You know, the pleasant thing about travelling is going back home.

1677
01:34:41,682 --> 01:34:44,106
It's like going away again.

1678
01:34:44,106 --> 01:34:46,621
Oh I had a good time. Didn't you, Andre?

1679
01:34:47,068 --> 01:34:47,778
Me?

1680
01:34:49,597 --> 01:34:52,757
I never laughed so much in my life.

1681
01:35:06,437 --> 01:35:07,440
You see, Pepe,

1682
01:35:08,093 --> 01:35:10,402
we meet at the appointed time.

1683
01:35:11,579 --> 01:35:12,840
Tell the truth.

1684
01:35:12,936 --> 01:35:14,707
I almost missed the appointment.

1685
01:35:18,757 --> 01:35:19,586
Not here.

1686
01:35:20,308 --> 01:35:20,955
As you wish.

1687
01:35:22,090 --> 01:35:24,392
I can't refuse an old friend.

1688
01:35:59,120 --> 01:36:02,104
All aboard who goes on board.

1689
01:36:24,823 --> 01:36:26,678
Let me wait here until it leaves.

1690
01:36:27,897 --> 01:36:29,268
It's not much to ask.

1691
01:36:31,358 --> 01:36:32,568
I can't get away.

1692
01:36:34,828 --> 01:36:36,263
I know I can trust you.

1693
01:37:29,540 --> 01:37:32,040
Gaby.

1694
01:37:37,517 --> 01:37:38,985
Gaby.

1695
01:37:40,046 --> 01:37:41,740
Gaby.

1696
01:37:41,979 --> 01:37:43,582
Gaby.

1697
01:37:44,476 --> 01:37:45,552
Gaby.

1698
01:37:53,438 --> 01:37:54,655
Gaby.

1699
01:37:58,679 --> 01:37:59,848
I'm sorry, Pepe.

1700
01:38:00,389 --> 01:38:02,377
He thought you were going to escape.

1701
01:38:04,598 --> 01:38:06,287
And

1702
01:38:06,322 --> 01:38:08,270
so I have,

1703
01:38:09,785 --> 01:38:11,057
my friend.

